    <text>
        <body>
            <div type="edition">
                <div type="textpart">
                    <ab><persName key="#Emperor/king" ref="#people/130">Henricus</persName> augustus
                            <rs key="#Emperor/king">imperator</rs> secundus accipit sub <rs
                            key="#Privileges">protectione imperiali</rs>
                        <rs key="#Monasteries">abbatiam</rs> et <rs key="#Exemption">liberam facit
                            ab omni subiectione <rs key="#Archbishops">archiepiscoporum</rs> sive
                            aliorum</rs>, ut sit regalis nulli subiecta personæ dominantium et
                        ipsius <rs key="#Monks">monachi</rs> a factione secularium immunes de suis
                        qualem voluerint <rs key="#Abbots">abbatem</rs> per <rs key="#Bishops"
                            >episcopum</rs>
                        <placeName ref="#places/485"><orgName
                                key="#Mother_churches #Bishops #Abbots"
                                ref="#juridical_persons/1498">Comaclensem</orgName></placeName>
                        consecrandum eligant. Confirmat ei, que ab <persName key="#Emperor/king"
                            ref="#people/7">Oddone</persName>
                        <rs key="#Emperor/king">imperatore</rs> tertio supra donata sunt et seu
                        concessa, videlicet ipsam abbatiam cum omnibus pertinentiis suis et cum
                        lateribus desuper in tota <rs key="#Islands">insula</rs>: primo latere
                            <placeName key="#Confinia #Rivers" ref="#places/4196">Pado</placeName>
                        percurrente in <rs key="#Sea">mare</rs>, secundo latere <rs key="#Shores"
                            >littus maris</rs>, tertio latere <placeName key="#Confinia #Rivers"
                            ref="#places/3563">Gauro</placeName>; insuper <rs key="#Fisheries"
                            >piscaria</rs> que vocatur <geogName key="#Fisheries"
                            ref="#estates/2457">Volana</geogName>, a <rs key="#Rivers">rivo</rs>
                        <placeName key="#Rivers" ref="#places/3575">Baderino</placeName> usque in
                        mare et locus qui dicitur <placeName ref="#places/3559">Lacu
                            Sancto</placeName> cum omnibus sibi pertinentibus, quantacumque in
                        apostolicê Sedis precepto releguntur, vel infra totum <rs key="#Comitatus"
                            >comitatum</rs>
                        <geogName ref="#estates/2449"><placeName ref="#places/485"
                                >Comaclensem</placeName></geogName> et <geogName ref="#estates/84"
                                ><placeName ref="#places/80">Ferrariensem</placeName></geogName> et
                            <geogName ref="#estates/2435"><placeName ref="#places/3538"
                                >Gavellensem</placeName></geogName> et in <rs key="#Cities"
                            >civitate</rs>
                        <placeName key="#Cities" ref="#places/594">Ravenna</placeName> et in
                        comitatu <geogName ref="#estates/2409"><placeName ref="#places/3512"
                                >Corneliense</placeName></geogName> et
                                <geogName><placeName>Faventino</placeName></geogName> et Liviense et
                        Pupiliense et Cesenate et Ariminense et Fanense et infra totum comitatum
                        Perusinum cum areis, êdificiis, castris, capellis, silvis, pratis, pascuis,
                        salictis, olivetis, vineis, montibus, planiciebus, aquis aquarumque
                        decursibus, piscationibus, venationibus, salinis et cum omni utilitate, quê
                        nominari aut scribi potest. Ostenditur bulla olim cereo sigillo roborata.
                        Inchoans: In nomine et individuê Trinitatis. Dat. VII kal. iulii, anno
                        Domini MXXII, indictione V, sui regni anno XXIo, imperii autem VIIIo.</ab>
                </div>
